children.value: it is essential to list every single KPI of every single department within your organization.
Later stages will focus on filtering these KPIs but in this step we will only be focusing on gathering every KPI in the organization.
we will be focusing on bringing the number of KPIs down to a manageable amount by looking into the importance and ease of measure of every single KPI.

By sorting the KPIs based on the importance and ease of measure we will bring down the total number of KPIs, this will lead to less clutter of KPI management and the gathering of the information to calculate the KPIs.
we will be gathering the meta-data behind the KPIs such as who is responsible for the KPI and what does the KPI cost to measure it?
This will give more insight and maybe lead to not measuring the KPI since it cost simply too much or isn’t that important after all.
By defining the KPIs you will get more insight in the KPIs that are being measured.
will provide you with information about the meta-data behind the KPIs.
This will give you insight on who is responsible for the most KPIs or what the most occurring problem is with the current list of KPIs.
Based on this information you can make it easier to measure the current list of KPIs.
This gives more freedom to do other tasks within the company.
Import an existing KPI tree or create one to begin the project
